  "meta": {
    "uuid": "aa277f37-1ebf-44ff-986a-6d9080b8ead2",
    "name": "SKEL-01: Production Planning",
    "summary": "Canonical manufacturing skeleton for production planning decisions. Captures what to produce, in what volume and mix, across which lines and shifts, and in what batch sequence. Five Action (Lever) nodes feed four Intermediate nodes which drive four Outcome nodes, with four External nodes providing uncontrollable inputs. All 17 variables from the KODI Lite Sprint Brief SKEL-01 specification are present.",
    "documentation": {
      "content": "KODI Lite Sprint \u00b7 Skeleton Library \u00b7 SKEL-01\n\nNode taxonomy by causalType:\n  Lever        (5)  \u2014 controllable scheduling decisions\n  External     (4)  \u2014 uncontrollable observed inputs\n  Intermediate (4)  \u2014 computed internal system states\n  Outcome      (4)  \u2014 final KPI-linked outputs\n\nDependency flow:\n  E \u2192 I  (8 edges): market/supply signals shape internal state\n  A \u2192 I  (11 edges): scheduling decisions drive system state\n  I \u2192 O  (8 edges): system state determines business outcomes\n  A \u2192 O  (3 edges): direct cost impact bypassing intermediates\n  E \u2192 O  (1 edge):  direct revenue impact from market conditions\n  O \u2192 O  (2 edges): fulfillment and unit cost cascade into gross margin\n\nTotal: 33 causal dependencies. Zero back-edges (no feedback loops).\n\nSchema compliance: OpenDI v0-draft-0325.\nKODI slot mapping for translation engine:\n  Lever        \u2192 A (Action)\n  External     \u2192 E (External)\n  Intermediate \u2192 I (Intermediate)\n  Outcome      \u2192 O (Outcome)\n",
      "MIMEType": "text/plain"
    },
    "version": "1.0",
    "draft": false,
    "createdDate": "2026-06-19T09:00:00Z"
  },
